
[1]pointed

   POINT'ED, pp. Sharpened; formed to a point; directed; aimed.

   1. Aimed at a particular person or transaction.

   2. a. Sharp; having a sharp point; as a pointed rock.

   3. Epigrammatical; abounding in conceits or lively turns; as pointed
   wit.
